author: Robyn Speer
commit_message:
Handle another indexing case from NumPy

NumPy arrays of integers have an __index__ method -- it's meant to apply
to scalars, and it raises an error if you actually try to run it on an
array.

These arrays are iterable, so if we move the is_iterable check first,
we won't encounter this error.

author: Kevin Kirsche
commit_message:
Fix incorrect use of `Any`

`Any` doesn't mean what it's being used here to indicate. Please see:
https://github.com/python/typeshed/pull/8469#issuecomment-1203116838

For an explanation of what `Any` means to a type checker. This replaces the use of `Any` with `object`, which is the actual "any object" behavior that was intended.

author: Kevin Kirsche
commit_message:
Simplify `_is_atomic` to use single isinstance call

When you want to check whether something is one of multiple different types, you can merge the two isinstance checks into a single call.

This is shorter while staying nice and easy to read.
